  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Dice the onions and courgettes. Thinly slice the spring onions and roughly chop the lettuce."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Preheat a large frying or sauté pan over a medium heat. Add a good glug of oil and tip in the onions and spring onions with a hefty pinch of salt. Cook for 4-5 mins, until just translucent, before adding the courgettes and half of the peas."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Cook for another 4-5 mins before adding the orzo. Start feeding the stock into the pan, a ladle at a time, stirring constantly, as if making a risotto. Once the pan has dried out, add a ladle more stock and continue like this until the orzo is fully cooked. This should take between 9-10 mins."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Make sure the mixture has a loose texture (add a bit more stock if it tightens up!) before tipping in the lettuce, broad beans, and artichokes. Toss through the orzo. Coarsely blitz the remaining peas in a nutribullet or with a hand blender. Tip into the pan and stir through the pasta."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Finish with the herbs and a good grating of Parm. Add a grating of lemon zest, plus a squeeze of juice right before serving."
    }
  ],
